    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s03.2.5" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Engine Coolant Temperature (ECT) Sensor</title>
        <figure id="f3450003008" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ09/J09014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>ECT sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The ECT sensor is a thermistor sensor. The ECM monitors the ECT signal and uses this information for the
            instrument panel temperature gauge, coolant compensation, Engine Warning Protection System (EWPS), and glow
            plug operation. The ECT sensor is installed in the left side of the front cover assembly.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
